(****************************************                                      **          M E D O S - 2               **          *************               **                                      **                                      **          ByteBlockIO:                **                                      **          File i/o routines for       **          - blocks (ARRAY OF WORD) &  **          - byteareas (addr, count)   **                                      **          Version 2   9.10.80         *    *                                      **                                      **          Svend Erik Knudsen          **          Institut fuer Informatik    **          ETH-Zuerich                 **          CH-8092 Zuerich             **                                      ****************************************)DEFINITION MODULE ByteBlockIO;   FROM FileSystem IMPORT File;  FROM SYSTEM IMPORT WORD, ADDRESS;  EXPORT QUALIFIED    ReadByteBlock, WriteByteBlock,    ReadBytes, WriteBytes;  PROCEDURE ReadByteBlock(VAR f: File; VAR block: ARRAY OF WORD);  PROCEDURE WriteByteBlock(VAR f: File; VAR block: ARRAY OF WORD);    PROCEDURE ReadBytes(VAR f: File; addr: ADDRESS; count: CARDINAL;                     VAR actualcount: CARDINAL);  PROCEDURE WriteBytes(VAR f: File; addr: ADDRESS; count: CARDINAL);END ByteBlockIO.  (* ReadByteBlock and WriteByteBlock transfer the given block      (ARRAY OF WORD) to or from the file f. The bytes are trans-     fered analog to ReadBytes and WriteBytes.     ReadBytes and WriteBytes transfer the given area (beginning      at address addr and with (count+1) DIV 2 words) to or from      the file f. The number of transfered bytes is returned in      actualcount. ReadBytes and WriteBytes transfer two bytes to     or from each word. If (actual-)count is odd, only one byte     (the upper one) is transfered to or from the last word.                                                                *)